<p><em>Your complete local guide to watching IPL 2026 in the Pink City — from parking hacks to the best biryani within walking distance of Sawai Mansingh Stadium.</em></p>
<p>Jaipur and cricket share a love story that goes back decades. The Sawai Mansingh Stadium — sitting proudly between Rambagh Palace and the Jaipur Golf Club — has witnessed some of Indian cricket's most electric moments. And IPL 2026 is about to add four more chapters to that story.</p>
<p>Rajasthan Royals are coming home to the Pink City for <strong>four blockbuster home matches</strong>, and whether you have a ticket in hand or you're watching from your favourite adda in Vaishali Nagar, this guide has everything you need to make the most of every match day in Jaipur.</p>
<p>Bookmark it. Share it with your group. You'll need it.</p>
<h2>Rajasthan Royals Home Matches in Jaipur — IPL 2026 Schedule</h2>
<p>Here are the four dates you need to mark in your calendar right now:</p>
<table><thead><tr><th>Match</th><th>Date</th><th>Opponent</th><th>Time</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Match 1</td><td><strong>Friday, April 25</strong></td><td>RR vs Sunrisers Hyderabad</td><td>7:30 PM IST</td></tr><tr><td>Match 2</td><td><strong>Friday, May 1</strong></td><td>RR vs Delhi Capitals</td><td>7:30 PM IST</td></tr><tr><td>Match 3</td><td><strong>Saturday, May 9</strong></td><td>RR vs Gujarat Titans</td><td>7:30 PM IST</td></tr><tr><td>Match 4</td><td><strong>Monday, May 19</strong></td><td>RR vs Lucknow Super Giants</td><td>7:30 PM IST</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>All four matches are at <strong>Sawai Mansingh Stadium, Jaipur</strong> — capacity 24,000. If you're going to the stadium, plan to arrive at least 90 minutes early. Gates fill up fast.</p>
<h2>Getting to Sawai Mansingh Stadium — The Local's Guide</h2>
<p><strong>Address:</strong> Sawai Mansingh Stadium, Bhawani Singh Road, Near Rambagh Circle, Jaipur — 302005</p>
<h3>By Auto / Cab</h3>
<p>Tell your driver “SMS Stadium” or “Rambagh wala stadium” — every auto driver in Jaipur knows it. Budget ₹80–₹150 from most parts of the city. On match days, use Ola/Uber for advance booking — surge pricing kicks in 30 minutes before the match starts.</p>
<h3>By Bus</h3>
<p>The nearest bus stops are <strong>Rambagh Circle</strong> (3-minute walk) and <strong>Nagar Nigam Lal Kothi</strong> (7-minute walk). Routes from Sindhi Camp, Ajmer Road, Tonk Road, and Vaishali Nagar all pass through Rambagh.</p>
<h3>By Train</h3>
<p>The two closest railway stations are <strong>Gandhinagar Railway Station</strong> (2.1 km) and <strong>Bais Godam</strong> (2.8 km). Jaipur Junction is about 4 km away — manageable by auto in 15 minutes outside peak traffic.</p>
<h3>Driving & Parking</h3>
<p>Parking near SMS Stadium is limited and chaotic on match days. The safest options:</p>
<ul><li><strong>Rajasthan University parking</strong> — 1.2 km walk, usually available</li><li><strong>SMS Medical College area</strong> — arrive 2+ hours early</li><li><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Park at Gaurav Tower or Panch Batti and take an auto the rest of the way. Saves 45 minutes of post-match traffic.</li></ul>
<h3>Roads to Avoid on Match Days</h3>
<p>Bhawani Singh Road gets completely jammed by 6:30 PM on match days. Come via Sardar Patel Marg or JLN Marg instead. Leave for home by 10:30 PM or be prepared to wait until 11:15 PM for traffic to clear.</p>
<h2>Where to Eat Near SMS Stadium Before the Match</h2>
<h3>Within Walking Distance (under 15 minutes)</h3>
<p><strong>Lassiwala Clone Wars — MI Road Area</strong><br />The stretch near Rambagh Circle has several good options for a quick pre-match meal. Head to the MI Road end early — after 6 PM, every decent place within 1 km of the stadium has a 20-minute wait.</p>
<p><strong>Niro's Restaurant (Civil Lines)</strong><br />Jaipur's most iconic restaurant is just 8 minutes from the stadium. Go for the dal baati churma thali if you want to eat well before a long evening. Book in advance on match days — they fill up by 6 PM.</p>
<p><strong>Handi Restaurant (near Rambagh)</strong><br />A Jaipur institution for Rajasthani food. The laal maas here is legendary. Perfect pre-match fuel. Moderate pricing, good portions.</p>
<p><strong>Spice Court (Jacob Road, Civil Lines)</strong><br />Set in a beautiful heritage courtyard. Their fixed Rajasthani thali is value for money. Slightly further (12 minutes by auto) but worth it for a proper sit-down meal.</p>
<h3>For Quick Bites Near the Gate</h3>
<p>The stretch on <strong>Bhawani Singh Road</strong> outside the stadium is lined with:</p>
<ul><li>Samosa and kachori sellers (₹10–₹20 per piece)</li><li>Cutting chai stalls — ask for “kadak wali”</li><li>Corn and bhutta vendors once the evening cools</li><li>RR merchandise stalls — jerseys, flags, foam fingers</li></ul>
<p>Budget ₹80–₹150 for a solid street food pre-match snack here.</p>
<h2>Best Places to Watch IPL 2026 Live in Jaipur Without Tickets</h2>
<p>Don't have a ticket? No problem. Jaipur has some fantastic spots to catch every ball with fellow fans. We'll update this list before every match with confirmed screening venues.</p>
<h3>Sports Bars & Pubs Screening IPL</h3>
<p><strong>1. 100% Rock — C-Scheme</strong><br />One of Jaipur's most popular sports screening venues. Multiple large screens, loud crowd, good drinks menu. Gets packed by 7 PM on match days — arrive by 6:30 PM or call ahead for a table.</p>
<p><strong>2. Blackout Bar & Kitchen — Tonk Road</strong><br />Popular with the 25–35 crowd. Good cocktail menu, enthusiastic atmosphere, screens visible from most seats. Limited seating — reservations recommended.</p>
<p><strong>3. The Brew House — Malviya Nagar</strong><br />Decent craft beer selection with solid big-screen viewing. Neighbourhood crowd makes for a friendly atmosphere. Less rowdy than city-centre spots.</p>
<p><strong>4. F Bar & Lounge — MI Road</strong><br />Central location, multiple screens, game-day specials on food and drinks. One of the easier spots to walk in and find a seat early in the season.</p>
<p><strong>5. Café Delhi Heights — Tonk Road</strong><br />For those who want good food with their cricket. Their sliders and nachos during the match are solid. More restaurant than sports bar but always screens IPL.</p>
<h3>Dhabas & Local Spots With Big Screens</h3>
<p>Hundreds of local dhabas, tea shops, and neighbourhood restaurants put up large TVs and projectors during IPL season. Check with your neighbourhood chaiwallah — chances are your colony's favourite corner shop has something set up.</p>
<p>We'll publish a neighbourhood-by-neighbourhood screening guide before each match on JaipurCircle. <strong>Subscribe to our WhatsApp channel</strong> for real-time updates on which spots have screens confirmed for each game.</p>
<h3>Watch Parties at Home — Make It Special</h3>
<p>If you're hosting, here's the Jaipur way to do it right:</p>
<ul><li>Order from <strong>Rawat Mishthan Bhandar</strong> (Sindhi Camp) — their pyaaz kachori is mandatory match food</li><li>Get <strong>Kaleva's</strong> sweets box for the 6s and 4s</li><li>Stock up on <strong>Aarav Shikanji</strong> from the local vendor for something cold and local</li></ul>
<h2>IPL Tickets for Jaipur Matches — How to Get Them</h2>
<p>Tickets for RR home matches at SMS Stadium sell out quickly. Here's where to find them:</p>
<p><strong>Official Channels:</strong></p>
<ul><li><strong>BookMyShow.com</strong> — primary ticketing partner, most reliable</li><li><strong>IPL official website</strong> (iplt20.com) — links to official ticketing</li><li><strong>Paytm Insider</strong> — check for availability, especially close to match day</li></ul>
<p><strong>Ticket Price Ranges (approximate):</strong></p>
<ul><li>General Enclosure: ₹500–₹800</li><li>Mid-tier stands: ₹1,200–₹2,000</li><li>Premium/Corporate boxes: ₹3,500–₹8,000+</li></ul>
<p><strong>Pro tips:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Check BookMyShow at midnight the night before a match — returns and re-releases often happen</li><li>Avoid buying from scalpers outside the stadium — counterfeits are common</li><li>The East Stand has the best view for the money in most price categories</li></ul>
<h2>Jaipur Weather During IPL Season — What to Expect</h2>
<p>April and May in Jaipur means heat. Here's what to prepare for:</p>
<ul><li><strong>April 25 evening match:</strong> Temperature drops to 22–26°C by 7:30 PM. Pleasant for cricket.</li><li><strong>May matches:</strong> Evenings are warmer — expect 28–34°C at 7:30 PM through May. Bring water, wear light cotton.</li><li><strong>Dust winds (Andhi):</strong> Rare but possible in May. SMS Stadium has some exposure to western winds.</li><li><strong>What to carry:</strong> Water bottle, light jacket for late-night return, and sunscreen if you arrive during daylight.</li></ul>
<h2>Neighbourhood Watch — Best Areas to Be On Match Day</h2>
<h3>Rambagh Circle Area</h3><p>The heart of match-day action. Every restaurant, chai stall, and paan shop has a TV up. The energy here from 6 PM to midnight on match days is something you have to experience.</p>
<h3>C-Scheme</h3><p>Jaipur's most vibrant dining and nightlife neighbourhood goes into overdrive on IPL evenings. Prithviraj Road and Sardar Chandra Road are lined with people watching from restaurants and cafés.</p>
<h3>Malviya Nagar</h3><p>The go-to neighbourhood for students and young professionals. Every second café and fast food joint has IPL on. Great for a budget match-day evening.</p>
<h3>Vaishali Nagar</h3><p>Jaipur's family neighbourhood comes alive with colony-level watch parties. Expect projector screens in parks and society lawns, local vendors setting up temporary stalls. Very Jaipur, very warm.</p>
<h3>Old City</h3><p>The experience of watching IPL from a rooftop haveli terrace in the Old City with the city walls lit up behind you is genuinely one of Jaipur's best kept secrets. If you have a connection in the walled city — use it on match night.</p>
