<h2>About Rajasthan Royals — Jaipur's Own</h2>
<p>The Rajasthan Royals were IPL's inaugural champions in 2008 — a fairytale first season under Shane Warne that Jaipur still talks about. The team has had its ups and downs since, but SMS Stadium has remained one of the most passionate home grounds in the league.</p>
<p>This season, Riyan Parag leads the side — a young Assamese captain with a flair for the dramatic. When RR plays at home in Jaipur, the city shows up. And when Jaipur shows up, it is loud.</p>
<h2>IPL 2026 Jaipur FAQs</h2>
<h3>Can I bring food and water inside SMS Stadium?</h3><p>Sealed water bottles up to 500ml are generally permitted. Outside food is usually not allowed — check the official ticket terms before each match as rules can vary.</p>
<h3>Is there a metro to SMS Stadium?</h3><p>The Jaipur Metro Phase 2 does not directly serve SMS Stadium yet. The nearest metro stations require a 15–20 minute auto ride. Bus remains the most convenient public transport option.</p>
<h3>What time do gates open at SMS Stadium?</h3><p>Typically 3 hours before match start — so around 4:30 PM for 7:30 PM games. Get there early to beat entry queues.</p>
<h3>Is SMS Stadium cashless?</h3><p>Most food and merchandise stalls inside are moving toward UPI / card payments. Carry some cash as backup.</p>
<h3>Are there family seating areas?</h3><p>Yes — check the seating map on BookMyShow when purchasing. Family enclosures are generally in the East and West stands.</p>
